race.comment: Tricky. ROSANGELA (10) resumes for a leading stable and brings strong form from tougher races. Her two jumpouts have been sharp and Mertens sticks from those. Races forward and she rates the one to beat. THAT'SMONEYBROTHER (4) is also in good hands and can build on his 1.3L defeat at Geelong on debut. Ethan Brown is a key jockey engagement. ESPANA (6) impressed her brief Maiden preparation in better city contests and has jumped out well for her return. Draws inside and Jamie Melham stays with her. A key player. MOTORSPORTS (9) debuts for the McEvoy yard and jumps from the inside barrier. Placed in a recent Flemington jumpout and the stable has a sharp record with newcomers.
